		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P>Nanyea wrote:<BR>definately some interesting posts here, I am curious as to why you would want channeling mastery, feign death has a very small fizzle/interupt as do the death's peace AA and I cant imagine you casting a dot while a mob is hitting you... is there perhaps something specific im not thinking of?</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>We are a CC class.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>With undead content finally being introduced consistantly, I find my role as a necromancer shifting in this direction more and more often. However, we are limited. We are limited by not having an undead tash/malo line to help assist us in our job and we are limited by our deficient survivability. We face higher resist rates than any other CC class and we are also the least equipped to handle hard hitting mobs. This is more than enough reason to justify the inclusion of this AA to our line up.</FONT><BR><BR>As far as asking for ways to remove agro, whats prompting this are the current tools not sufficient, in what particular ways are they lacking and what could be done to improve them, and on the opposite hand in what instances would you like to keep your agro, actually giving examples of why and how you would use something tends to be more helpful then saying can I get this and not giving a reasoning why (stuff like we didnt get a big enough DPS increase this expansion isnt particuarly helpful)</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>We have the abilty to shed aggro instantly. Our aggro should be viewed as a tool to assist us in doing our CC job. For years I relied on poison aggro to draw adds away from a group in order to CC it with root. This was nerfed in a prior patch and never fully addressed. Asking for aggro to be reduced is foolish and stinks of poor management skills.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>Again, we dont have an aggro problem. Why? Because we can FD.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>Its the ultimate aggro management tool. If&nbsp;folks dont know how, they need to learn.</FONT><BR><BR>Kinda off topic from some other threads, but as far as getting a new pet model, there are several other classes that would like to get in on a new pet model and illusions (mind you we are getting a new one with the new expansion that will be itemized out to rogues/bards), then again anything that has to do with the global file and revamping always tends to run to the slow.</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>Ill leave this alone. I have no problems with the spectre pet, and ill miss him when hes gone. But I understand this is a concern for many of us. Although I think its a waste of resources, I wont fight it that people want this updated.</FONT><BR><BR>As a personal suggestion to Sauramaan/Apokalypse&gt;? perhaps the way you post things is whats coming off as abrasive to your community and others is the lack of a coherent thread between what you post and the information you are gathering from various sources to present as "your collected information" and that that breakdown is why people are coming down on you... I do read several of the necro boards (among others) and theres nothing wrong with presenting a pet idea or something new that you have come up with, but to present that as the will of the community is well... reprehensible for lack of a better word</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>As another suggestion, how about being a little visible and showing a little bit of interest. We never see you speak up the way other CC's do. Take a few tips from the warrior CC and others. Sure they are bigmouths, but sometimes&nbsp;thats what it takes to call attention to our needs. Being invisible doesnt do squat.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>And also, how about a little organization. There are suggestion posts all over the place. While I commend the attempt to gain feedback, there&nbsp;are posts&nbsp;scattered across several class boards. I dont know about anyone else, but I can barely make sense of it and I put forth an effort to try. Its no wonder our lists turn out to be a hodgepodge of strung out complaints, we can never get consensus of what direction you plan to go. Sometimes I wonder if you even play the game anymore. It seems like youre on a hiatus until you pop up and toss a question into the wind.</FONT><BR><BR>Much love to all the Class Correspondents for doing a thankless job</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>Yes.</FONT><BR><BR>p.s. I suks at dah spellings~<BR></P>
