		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>As a necro, I agree that we can just fd and be done with it regarding extra dot aggro.&nbsp; However, as a raidleader and guild officer, I still want something to be done about it.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Well, shamans come to mind as well as wizards.&nbsp; I'd like for them to have the ability to invest in and use&nbsp;dot crit AA's (or Pyromancy for wizards) without worrying about unintended aggro.&nbsp; Shaman dd/rain spells suck for efficiency, and not using Pyromancy is giving up a 1500 total damage dot.&nbsp; There are so many issues that affect several classes at once and too often, no one steps up because they expect someone else to do the work.&nbsp; Many times, I don't bother memm'ing pets for raids because of AE rampage and pets exploding on the first hit, however, it's the mages that have done the brunt of the work for trying to get a resolution for that.&nbsp; Necros and beastlords have made some noise about it but not nearly to the extent as mages have.&nbsp; It was also the mages that got pet foci progression smoothed out and the pathetic CoA focus improved after it came out.&nbsp; Sure,&nbsp;the vast majority&nbsp;of the dot damage out there comes from necros and we have learned how to deal with it for the most part.&nbsp; However, the other dotting classes have no reliable way to deal with extra unintended aggro.</P>
<P>Before you blow it off, think about this:&nbsp;before we had a tradeskill correspondent, Rune of Zephyr NEVER dropped in the game, therefore, it was impossible to research certain spells including Mask of the Stalker, a lvl 60 druid/65 ranger FT buff, which&nbsp;was selling for 25k YEARS after the spell came out simply because the only source for the spell were raid targets until it was fixed.&nbsp; This issue was number one on the tradeskill Top 10 on the very first list.&nbsp; I don't know of any dot correspondent&nbsp;and I don't know of any other class that can say that this affects us so drastically that it is a REQUIREMENT for us to get an AA to be able to begin to deal with getting dot crit AA and dot dmg foci.</P>
<P>Just my 2 cp.</P>	
