		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Sauruman,</P>
<P><STRONG>"How do the developers view necromancers as a class evolving over time?"</STRONG></P>
<P>The single question&nbsp;of that entire post in its elemental&nbsp;essense. Is what you are asking for is a common frame of reference for all necromancers and the dev team, a "Class Definition" if you like. The question is an unwise one to ask as the Dev team is obstinate in the fact that they will not give the player base the common frame of reference necessary to redefine and refine our views for the&nbsp; class in the future.</P>
<P>It is an open ended question, so I believe will have no answer. The reason? When they have the player base will twist and twirl, will parse and analyse and then hold the Dev's onto every word. Druid stances are a classic example.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P></P>
<HR>
Jugatta wrote: 
<P>Necromancers can't mez because there are Enchanters for that.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Necromancers have Mez, Charm and Slows specifically with use against the undead. I am of the opinion that they should be as useful to the levels against what an enchanter do, against the undead, the enchanter has other tools at their command not to mention ability to mez live mobs which would not significantly inhibit their group desirability.</P>
<P>These abilities are current live spells (Mez/Charm) they are not relics of ages past, they should update them properly.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P></P>
<HR>
Jugatta wrote: 
<P></P>
<P></P>
<P>Undead Nukes are the only thing I can see being upgraded. We shouldnt have to nuke 10 times to match 1 hit of a pallys sword.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P>We&nbsp;share the same ones as the cleric. The cleric is under their own "class balance" issues, with the other priests. As such a new line is required (which would be unlikely) or we just take these as relics. We have plenty of other damaging abilities. I still think a mini-crit should occur with cleric and necromancer undead nukes (similar but weaker&nbsp;to the Turn Undead AA), which if the planets align would give 7+k crit</P></BLOCKQUOTE><p>Message Edited by corvardus on <span class=date_text>07-10-2006</span> <span class=time_text>11:56 AM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<hr><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1281938&resize=true>Horcrux SoulImbiber</a><b> Guktan Grand Occultis</b>t<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=636624&resize=true>Corvard Pasodonia</a> <b>Prelate O'Brell</b><br><b>Druzzil Ro</b>
							</div>
								
